      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "When tackling Hollywood tropes, being aware of their potential impacts is key. Here are 5 common racial stereotypes to be cautious of and subvert:\n\n1. The 'Tough but Loyal' African American Sidekick: Avoid portraying a strong, skilled sidekick who serves solely to support the white protagonist.\n2. The Nerdy Asian Male: Steer clear of making your Asian character just an expert in technology or accounting, and give them depth and nuance.\n3. The Sassy Latina Love Interest: Don't rely on Latina characters as seductive or comedic relief; give them agency and interesting storylines.\n4. The Mongolian Warrior/Exotic Eastern Dancer: Be wary of exoticizing cultures by relying on traditional dress and interests as a shorthand for entire cultures.\n5. The Intellectual Stereotype (mainly Asian or Indian): Avoid making your character a token genius or expert; instead, make them an egalitarian, multidimensional individual. \n\nBy acknowledging and critiquing these tropes, you can create a more nuanced and inclusive script.",
